                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d892">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13040.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 28. It is my impression that General Carranza, in accordance
                    with the Mexican spirit, wishes to arrange the meeting himself if possible. If
                    he discovers he cannot arrange it, then he will use the good offices of the
                    United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
